Given a right triangle with a 24-inch leg and a 25-inch hypotenuse, find the area of the triangle in square inches.Let's denote the right triangle as $	riangle ABC$, where:- $\overline{AC}$ is the hypotenuse with length 25 inches- $\overline{AB}$ is the known leg with length 24 inches- $\overline{BC}$ is the unknown leg egin{tikzpicture}\draw (0,0) -- (4,0) -- (4,3) -- cycle;\draw (2,0) -- (2,0.2) -- (1.8,0.2) -- (1.8,0);
ode at (2,-0.3) {$B$};
ode at (4.3,0) {$C$};
ode at (4,3.3) {$A$};
ode at (2.2,1.5) {$24$};
ode at (4.2,1.5) {$?$};
ode at (3,2.5) {$25$};\end{tikzpicture}The goal is to find the area of $	riangle ABC$.
